# Assist Platform rules

Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/START_HERE.md` before editing.

- One shared PHP/MariaDB application serves VanAssist, TowSmart and TrailerWise.
- Use the typed brand registry and request brand context; never infer a tenant
  from an arbitrary production query parameter.
- Preserve VanAssist compatibility and all existing production data.
- Use forward-only migrations. Never edit applied migrations or reset production.
- Enforce permissions, brand scope and ownership server-side.
- Never reveal or commit secrets, passwords, tokens, private documents or dumps.
- Keep TowSmart formulas pure, tested and non-authoritative.
- Do not represent planned or partial functionality as complete.
- Every behavioural change needs tests and documentation proportional to risk.
- Before completion run the checks in `docs/TESTING.md` and report skipped or
  unavailable checks honestly.
- Production deployments follow `docs/OPERATIONS_RUNBOOK.md`; application code
  changes alone do not authorise deployment, DNS changes or live migrations.

